article.headline: Auburn 71, Troy 68
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Frank Tolbert scored on a tip-in with 18 seconds left and then hit two free throws to seal Auburn's 71-68 season-opening victory over Troy Friday night. The Tigers rallied from a nine-point deficit early in the second half and scored the game's final seven points. Troy took a 68-64 lead on Richard Chaney's 3-pointer with 1:25 left. Auburn's Quantez Robertson answered 20 seconds later with another 3. After a Troy miss, Tolbert tipped in Rasheem Barrett's missed 3-pointer for the lead. Korvotney Barber, who had 13 points and 16 rebounds, then knocked away O'Darien Bassett's layup attempt with 9 seconds left. The seconds ticked away as the Trojans had to commit three fouls to put Auburn in a free throw shooting situation. Tolbert hit his two foul shots with 2 seconds left, and Barber's steal prevented Troy from getting off a potential tying shot. Tolbert finished with 14 points and eight rebounds. Quantez Robertson had 12 points and Barrett 11 for the Tigers, who outrebounded Troy 54-38. Chaney led the Trojans with 21 points and 12 rebounds. Bassett added 13 points and Jerome Odem had 11. The Tigers have won all 10 meetings in the series. They opened the season without suspended forwards Josh Dollard and Quan Prowell.
